# AI Global OS

**Root:** `D:/server/.ai`

## Cold Start (EVERY session)

1. Read `D:/server/.ai/global-roles.md` — load persona, quality gates, and absolute prohibitions
2. Read `D:/server/.ai/global-workflow.md` — load execution protocol and context layers
3. Check `D:/server/.ai/manifest.json` — route task to correct workflow

## Context Layers (lazy)

| Layer | Load | When |
|-------|------|------|
| 0 | `rules/core-behavioral-compact.md`, `skills/` | Always |
| 1 | `rules/vocabulary.md`, `rules/anti-patterns.md`, `tech-stack/useful-repos.md` | Always |
| 2 | `rules/*.md`, `tech-stack/` files matching detected stack | On demand |
| 3 | `workflows/*.md` | Per task type |

Detect stack via `package.json` / `composer.json` in current project root.
Load `spec.md` from current project root if it exists.

## Active Context

Check `{project_root}/.ai/active-context.md` for current sprint/task state (per-project file, not in global OS).
If missing, fall back to `D:/server/.ai/state/MEMORY.md` for cross-project persistent state.

## Absolute Prohibitions (always active)

- ⛔ NO `min/` folders — rules are natively compressed
- ⛔ NO unauthorized server actions — explicit user approval required
- ⛔ NO generic UIs — apply `tech-stack/design-foundations.md`
- ⛔ NO partial work — zero linter warnings, SOLID/DRY/KISS enforced
- ⛔ NO blind code generation — if requirements < 80% clear, STOP and ask
- ⛔ NO destructive bash without validation
- ⛔ DO NOT rely on cached context for core rules — re-read on every cold start

## Symbolic Codes

Full dictionary in `D:/server/.ai/rules/vocabulary.md`.
`[BEH-xx]` behavior · `[SEC-xx]` security · `[EXE-xx]` execution · `[QA-xx]` quality

## Handoff

On milestone completion run `D:/server/.ai/workflows/09-memory-sync.md`.
